<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-277-297  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 277 297.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>InfoWorld  Jan 23 1989 v11 n4 p40(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Beware of companies that fan flames of computer virus fear.andO;(column)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Parker, Rachel.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Companies that market software and hardware to protect againstcomputer viruses are guilty of spreading false alarms and hysteriaabout potentially damaging viruses.andP;  These companies have gottenthe attention of the mass media in their efforts to unduly alarmthe user community about viruses.andP;  The Software EntrepreneursForum is one organization that is making a credible effort tocombat viruses.andP;  The Forum is creating a code segment thatdevelopers can put into commercial software so the commercialprograms will have the ability to monitor systems for intrusion.andO;The problem of computer viruses is real, and it representspotential disaster of overwhelming proportions.andP;  But dealing withproblems and trading on fear are two distinct activities.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Computer VirusesComputer CrimesManufacturersAccess ControlsMarketing Strategy.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>